# Clean Code Function Standards

## Context
- These rules ensure functions are small and focused
- They promote maintainable and testable code

## Requirements
1. Keep functions small
2. Do one thing
3. Use descriptive names
4. Prefer fewer arguments
5. Have no side effects
6. Avoid flag arguments

## Examples
<example>
// Good: Small, focused function
function calculateTotalPrice(items: Item[]): number {
  return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0);
}
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// Bad: Multiple responsibilities, flag parameter
function processItems(items: Item[], shouldCalculate: boolean, shouldSort: boolean) {
  // Multiple responsibilities based on flags
}
</example>

## Critical Rules
- NEVER write functions longer than 20 lines
- ALWAYS ensure functions do one thing
- NEVER use flag arguments
- ALWAYS use descriptive function names 
